-- Trinity Mirror Shareholders Call for CEO Pay Cut, Times Reports
-- B y   A g n e s   L o v a s z
-- 2012-03-11T09:00:23Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-11/trinity-mirror-shareholders-call-for-ceo-pay-cut-times-reports.html
Trinity Mirror Plc (TNI)  shareholders,
including  Schroders Plc (SDR) ,  Aviva Plc (AV/) ,  Standard Life Plc (SL/)  and  Legal
& General Group Plc (LGEN) , are calling for a reduction in the pay
package of Sly Bailey, the publisher’s chief executive, the
Sunday Times reported.  Bailey’s remuneration is due to be discussed at a Trinity
Mirror board meeting before March 15 when the company is
scheduled to announce quarterly results, the newspaper said,
without saying how it got the information.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Agnes Lovasz in London at 
 alovasz@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Balazs Penz at 
 bpenz@bloomberg.net  